UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee v. Adrian ARZATE-DIAZ DE LEON, also known as Adrian Arzate-Leon, Defendant-Appellant. No. 09-51024

Summary Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Nov. 15, 2010. Joseph H. Gay, Jr., Assistant U.S. Attorney, U.S. Attorney’s Office, San Antonio, TX, for Plaintiff-Appellee. Maria B. Ramirez, El Paso, TX, for Defendanb-Appellant. Before REAVLEY, DENNIS, and CLEMENT, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM: *

The attorney appointed to represent Adrian Arzate-Diaz de Leon has moved for leave to withdraw and has filed a brief in accordance with Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Arzate-Diaz de Leon has not filed a response. Our independent review of the record and counsel’s brief discloses no nonfrivolous issue for appeal. Accordingly, counsel’s motion for leave to withdraw is GRANTED, counsel is excused from further responsibilities herein, and the APPEAL IS DISMISSED. See 5th Cir. R. 42.2.

Pursuant to 5th Cir. R. 47.5, the court has determined that this opinion should not be published and is not precedent except under the limited circumstances set forth in 5th Cir. R. 47.5.4.
